    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix WAITMSG3 state handling in schedule_RA function\n\n### Summary\nThe `schedule_RA()` function in the eNB scheduler was not properly handling the WAITMSG3 state of random access procedures. When an RA process transitioned to WAITMSG3 state, the function would skip processing it entirely, leading to missed Msg3 scheduling opportunities and potential RRC connection setup failures.\n\nThis issue manifested as UEs failing to complete the random access procedure, with Msg3 transmissions not being properly scheduled in the uplink. The problem was particularly noticeable in high load scenarios where multiple UEs were attempting to connect simultaneously.\n\nThe root cause was a missing case statement for the WAITMSG3 state in the main RA scheduling loop. This fix adds proper handling for WAITMSG3 that checks if the current frame/subframe matches the Msg3 timing and logs the active state appropriately.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_RA.c`: Added WAITMSG3 state handling in schedule_RA function with frame/subframe matching and logging\n"
}